*xfig-3.2.4-r1 (10 Mar 2003)

  10 Mar 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> xfig-3.2.4-r1.ebuild,
  files/xfig-3.2.4-xaw3d.diff:
  supports Xaw3d now. thanks to: Sander Graswinckel <sgraswinckel@hotmail.com>
  for the patch in bug #16224

*xfig-3.2.4 (12 Feb 2003)

  12 Feb 2003; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> xfig-3.2.4.ebuild :

  Version bump thanks to: Daniele Foci <sunscan@sunscan.org> in bug
  #14245.  Also, removed the patch from files and sent it to the mirrors,
  and using epatch from eutils.eclass to handle the patching.

*xfig-3.2.3d-r1 (13 Apr 2002)

  07 Jan 2003; George Shapovalov <george@gentoo.org> xfig-3.2.3d-r1.ebuild :
  added IUSE, few cosmetic touch-ups

  02 Dec 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> xfig-3.2.3d-r1.ebuild :

  Added media-libs/netpbm to RDEPEND, closing bug #11515 by ntl@swt.edu
  (nate lynch)

  7 Sep 2002; Owen Stampflee <owen@gentoo.org> :
  Added PPC to KEYWORDS.

  13 Apr 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> xfig-3.2.3d-r1.ebuild :

  Added transfig to the RDEPEND. Did not bump version numbers though.
  Closes bug #1619 by ekoontz@hiro-tan.dhs.org (Eugene Koontz)

*xfig-3.2.3d (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
